com.calendarfx.model

Class CalendarEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.EventObject
      • javafx.event.Event
        • com.calendarfx.model.CalendarEvent
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable

    public class CalendarEvent
extends Event
    An event class used to signal changes done within a calendar or changes done to a calendar entry. Events of this type can be received by adding an event handler to a calendar.

    Example

     
 Calendar calendar = new Calendar("Home");
 calendar.addEventHandler(CalendarEvent.ENTRY_ADDED, evt -> {...});
    See Also:
    Calendar.addEventHandler(javafx.event.EventHandler), Serialized Form

        public static final EventType<CalendarEvent> ENTRY_FULL_DAY_CHANGED
        An event type used to inform the application that an entry has become a "full day" entry, meaning its start and end time are no longer relevant. The entry should be visualized in a way that signals that the entry will take all day (e.g. a birthday).

      • isEntryAdded

        public final boolean isEntryAdded()
        A utility method to determine if the event describes the creation of a new entry. This is the case when the event type is ENTRY_CALENDAR_CHANGED and the old calendar was null.
        Returns:
        true if the event describes the creation of a new entry

      • isEntryRemoved

        public final boolean isEntryRemoved()
        A utility method to determine if the event describes the removal of an entry. This is the case when the event type is ENTRY_CALENDAR_CHANGED and the old calendar was not null but the new calendar is null.
        Returns:
        true if the event describes the removal of a new entry

      • isDayChange

        public final boolean isDayChange()
        Determines whether the event will have an impact on different days. The method will return false if the user simply changed the start and / or end time of an entry within the current day. However, when the user drags the entry from one day to another then this method will return true.
        Returns:
        true if the new time interval of the entry touches other days than the old time interval of the entry
